        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over North Wilkesboro, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail and wind gusts up to 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Loose objects may be knocked over by wind gusts.

Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Wilkesboro...
Ronda...
Traphill...
Mc Grady...
Mulberry...
and Roaring Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
